      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add development trace UI",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nWhen debugging OpenClaw model calls locally, there's no way to inspect the exact raw payloads — prompts, tool schemas, parameters, streaming responses — that are actually sent to and received from LLM providers.\n\n## Solution\n\nA development-only in-memory trace recorder and a Phoenix-style Traces view in the Control UI. Start the Gateway with `OPENCLAW_DEV_EXTENDED_TRACING=1` from a source checkout, open `/traces`, and see exactly what each model call sent and received.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/cb14c776-7110-4ebc-bbbe-ae04d026bda2\n\n## Architecture\n\nFour layers:\n\n**Recording** — Two integration points feed traces into the store:\n- The pi-embedded-runner's existing `wrapStreamFnWithDiagnosticModelCallEvents` wrapper is extended to record start, request payload (captured *after* caller `onPayload` mutations), response chunks, and completion/error with timing metadata.\n- Codex app-server turns get their own bridging since they don't use the standard `StreamFn` wrapping — a `buildCodexDevTraceRequestPayload` assembles instructions, input, tools, and history, and notifications are mapped to response chunks for TTFB tracking.\n\n**Storage** (`src/infra/llm-dev-tracing.ts`) — Module-level in-memory ring buffer (200 traces, 100 response chunks per trace). All values are `structuredClone`d on write and read to prevent mutation. All recording functions are no-ops when tracing is disabled.\n\n**Gateway** (`src/gateway/server-methods/traces.ts`) — Three new methods at `operator.admin` scope:\n- `traces.capabilities` — reports whether tracing is available for this client\n- `traces.list` — returns all trace summaries\n- `traces.get` — returns a single trace with full request payload and response chunks\n\n**UI** (`ui/src/ui/views/traces.ts`) — Trace list sidebar + detail pane with collapsible sections for prompt messages, history messages, tool schemas with argument tables, invocation parameters, reconstructed response text, and raw JSON disclosures for everything. Lazy-loaded; hidden from the sidebar when tracing is unavailable.\n\n## Protocol changes\n\nThree additive Gateway methods (`traces.capabilities`, `traces.list`, `traces.get`). No version bump, no changes to existing methods, no new handshake fields. Old clients that don't know about `traces.*` simply never call them. The `isLocalClient` and `allowsDevLlmTracing` fields on `GatewayClient`/`GatewayWsClient` are server-internal and don't appear on the wire.\n\n## Security model\n\nTraces contain raw prompts and tool payloads, which may include private content. Access requires **all** of:\n\n1. Running from a source checkout (not npm/packaged install)\n2. `OPENCLAW_DEV_EXTENDED_TRACING=1` in the environment\n3. Admin scope on the Gateway connection\n4. Browser Control UI client (not CLI, not webchat)\n5. Loopback socket address (127.0.0.1 / ::1)\n6. Loopback Host and Origin headers\n7. No proxy forwarding headers (X-Forwarded-For, etc.)\n\nThis means the trace methods stay disabled for packaged installs, Tailscale/LAN/public deployments, and reverse-proxied sessions even if the env flag is set.\n\n## Verification\n\n<details>\n<summary>Test commands</summary>\n\n```\npnpm docs:list\npnpm exec oxfmt --check src/infra/llm-dev-tracing.ts src/agents/llm-dev-tracing.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/traces.test.ts scripts/gateway-watch-tmux.mjs src/infra/gateway-watch-tmux.test.ts\npnpm exec oxfmt --check ui/src/ui/views/traces.ts ui/src/styles/components.css ui/src/ui/e2e/traces.e2e.test.ts\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/llm-dev-tracing.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/traces.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.model-diagnostic-events.test.ts --reporter=verbose\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/infra/gateway-watch-tmux.test.ts --reporter=verbose\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.ui-e2e.config.ts --configLoader runner ui/src/ui/e2e/traces.e2e.test.ts --reporter=verbose\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.test.ts -t \"fires llm_input, llm_output, and agent_end hooks for codex turns\" --reporter=verbose\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run ui/src/styles/components.test.ts --reporter=verbose\npnpm tsgo:prod\npnpm ui:build\ngit diff --check\nrg -n \"OPENCLAW_DEV_(TRACING_UI|TRACE_LLM_PAYLOADS|TRACE_LLM_RESPONSE)\" src scripts docs ui CHANGELOG.md  # no matches\nOPENCLAW_GATEWAY_WATCH_ATTACH=0 OPENCLAW_DEV_EXTENDED_TRACING=1 pnpm gateway:watch\npnpm openclaw dashboard --no-open\n```\n\n</details>\n",
